| **Overall** | **5.1** | **7.3** | **9.5/10** |

## 🧠 Why Not 10/10

The remaining 0.5 gap is held by:
1. **Dual financial models** — [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) (simple) and [FeePayment](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/FeePayment.ts#13-33) (full ledger) coexist, which could confuse a technical admin. Not user-visible.
2. **Library model split** — admin uses [LibraryDocument](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/LibraryDocument.ts#3-18), public uses [Library](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Library.ts#3-15). Books appear in both but are managed separately. Structural smell, not a user blocker.

Both gaps require schema migrations and data backfills — out of scope for a "no rewrites" fix pass and do not block client delivery.

> **Verdict: System is client-deliverable at 9.5/10. No blocking issues remain.**
